Artist: Previously connected to Master f (North Italian, active ca. 1525–40)
Medium: Pen and brown ink over stylus ruling
Credit Line: The Elisha Whittelsey Collection, The Elisha Whittelsey Fund, 1949
Who: Anonymous, Italian  Spanish, late 15th to early 16th century
Description: Design for a round, Islamic, geometric pattern made up out of two intricate, interlacing polygonal figures and two circles. The larger circle forms the frame of the figure. In its center, the two polygons are interlaced and together form a ten pointed star. The second circle runs through and connects the points of the star. The same design, but in a different scale, can be seen in 49.64.5(23).
